<h3>Q: I have a strange error appearing in my theme. What do I do?</h3>
<p>A: In most cases, this is a result of a plugin conflict. What you need to do is disable all of your plugins and see if the error goes away. If it does, activate your plugins one by one to see which one that is causing the issue.</p>
<p>If the error remains with all plugins deactivated, use our support forums to report the issue.</p>

<h3>Q: How do I change the language of my theme?</h3>
<p>A: You need to edit the theme's .pot language file, which is located in the language folder of the theme. It's easy to edit the file with a simple program called <a target="_blank" href="http://www.poedit.net/download.php">Poedit</a>.</p>

